{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-nyctibius-leucopterus", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-nyctibius-leucopterus", "name": "White-winged potoo", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-species-nyctibius-leucopterus", "name": "White-winged potoo", "latinName": "Nyctibius leucopterus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "White-winged potoo（Nyctibius leucopterus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如White-winged potoo。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": 885.46, "y": -175.44, "z": 104.9}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-nyctibius", "name": "钩嘴夜鹰属", "latinName": "Nyctibius", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "钩嘴夜鹰属（Nyctibius）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联7种鸟类，如Rufous potoo、Great potoo、Long-tailed potoo等7种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 7, "x": 278.49, "y": -599.74, "z": -2.58}, {"id": "bird-white-winged-potoo-d97ba7ff", "name": "White-winged potoo", "englishName": "White-winged potoo", "latinName": "Nyctibius leucopterus", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The white-winged potoo (Nyctibius leucopterus) is a species of bird in the family Nyctibiidae. It is found in Brazil, French Guiana, Guyana, Peru, Suriname, and Venezuela. Taxonomy and systematics For a time the Andean potoo (Nyctibius maculosus) was considered a subspecies of the white-winged potoo, but size, plumage, voice, and elevational distribution differentiate them. Those two species, the northern potoo (N. jamaicensis), and the common potoo (N. griseus) are more closely related to each other than to the other potoos. The white-winged potoo is (as of 2021) considered to be monotypic, but the Amazonian form might be a species in its own right. Description The white-winged potoo has two forms that differ significantly in size but are almost identical otherwise. The species as a whole is 24 to 29 cm (9.4 to 11.4 in) long. The Amazonian form weighs 77 to 85 g (2.7 to 3.0 oz); it is much smaller than the eastern one though the latter's weight has not been documented. Both forms are dark brown above and lighter brown below, and both parts have darker speckles. The large white patch on the secondary wing coverts give the species its name. Distribution and habitat The Amazonian form of white-winged potoo is known from scattered sites in the Amazon basin of Eastern Venezuela, eastern Peru, the Guianas, and northern Brazil, though it probably occurs throughout the region. There it inhabits the canopy of mature terra firme rainforest, including forest on white-sand soils. In the early 2000s researchers made several sightings along the Amazon on poor but non-sandy soils between areas of white-sand forest. The eastern form has a much smaller range in Brazil's Bahia and Espírito Santo states. It is not well known but is assumed to inhabit the canopy of the Atlantic Forest. Behavior Feeding The white-winged potoo is nocturnal. It captures its insect prey by sallying from an exposed perch. Breeding The white-winged potoo's breeding phenology is unknown. It is assumed to lay one egg on a branch high in the canopy in a manner similar to that of other potoos. Vocalization The song of the Amazonian form of white-winged potoo is \"a gradually descending, pure-toned 'feeeoooooo'\" described as haunting and melancholy. It also makes a soft \"bweep\" call. Status The IUCN has assessed the white-winged potoo as being of Least Concern, though its population is unknown and thought to be decreasing. In Amazonia, \"the biggest threat comes from continued destruction of pristine forest.\" References External links Graphic; Article ao.com.br", "shortSummary": "The white-winged potoo (Nyctibius leucopterus) is a species of bird in the family Nyctibiidae. It is found in Brazil, French Guiana, Guyana…", "locations": ["法屬圭亞那", "圭亚那", "蘇利南", "委內瑞拉", "森林", "雨林", "巴伊亞州", "圣埃斯皮里图州"], "lat": -10.0, "lng": -52.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Nyctibius_leucopterus_White-winged_Potoo%3B_Presidente_Figueiredo%2C_Amazonas%2C_Brazil_%28cropped%29.jpg/960px-Nyctibius_leucopterus_White-winged_Potoo%3B_Presidente_Figueiredo%2C_Amazonas%2C_Brazil_%28cropped%29.jpg", "order": "Caprimulgiformes", "family": "Nyctibiidae", "genus": "Nyctibius", "species": "Nyctibius leucopterus", "orderCn": "夜鷹目", "familyCn": "钩嘴夜鹰科", "genusCn": "钩嘴夜鹰属", "speciesCn": "White-winged potoo", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "orderId": "taxonomy-order-caprimulgiformes", "familyId": "taxonomy-family-nyctibiidae", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-nyctibius", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-nyctibius-leucopterus", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "order": "taxonomy-order-caprimulgiformes", "family": "taxonomy-family-nyctibiidae", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-nyctibius", "species": "taxonomy-species-nyctibius-leucopterus"}, "expandable": true, "x": 885.46, "y": -175.44, "z": 116.76}], "links": [{"key": "bird-white-winged-potoo-d97ba7ff__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-nyctibius-leucopterus", "source": "bird-white-winged-potoo-d97ba7ff", "target": "taxonomy-species-nyctibius-leucopterus", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-nyctibius-leucopterus__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-nyctibius", "source": "taxonomy-species-nyctibius-leucopterus", "target": "taxonomy-genus-nyctibius", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：White-winged potoo 属于属 钩嘴夜鹰属。"}]}
